# Applications in Database Systems

Balanced trees play an important role in modern database architectures.

## Red-Black Tree Applications

Commonly used in:

* In-memory indexing structures
* Operating system scheduling algorithms
* Balanced associative containers

## B-Tree Applications

Widely used in:

* Database indexing
* File system metadata management
* Storage engines
* Query processing systems

Most relational database systems rely on B-Tree indexes because they provide excellent performance while minimizing disk I/O operations.

